<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1194" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1194">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">860C.01/7–2744: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the Chairman of the Council of
                                    People’s Commissars of the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stalin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-27">27 July,
                                    1944</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>31. Your telegram regarding the Polish situation has been
                                    received.<note n="51" xml:id="d1194fn51">See footnote 86, <ref target="#pg_1424">p. 1424</ref>.</note> The Prime Minister
                                tells me that Mikolajczyk is leaving to call on you. It is
                                unnecessary to say that I greatly hope this whole matter with him
                                can be worked out to the best advantage of our common effort by
                                you.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>